name: AcuteMyocardialInfarctionAMI
title: Acute Myocardial Infarction (AMI)
purpose: (Clinical Focus: This set of values contains diagnoses used to identify patients with acute myocardial infarction.),(Data Element Scope: The intent of this data element is to identify patients with a diagnosis of acute myocardial infarction. Using the Quality Data Model, this particular element would map to the Diagnosis, Active data type.),(Inclusion Criteria: Include diagnosis codes that describe acute myocardial infarction with initial or unspecified episodes of care.),(Exclusion Criteria: Exclude codes that describe complications and history of myocardial infarction.)
